enterField(Worker) - Method in class world.FlowerField
When a worker bee requests entry in to the field, you should first display a message:

*FF* {bee} enters field

There is only one condition that would cause a bee to have to wait - if there are no flowers because all the other bees are gathering from them.
equals(Object) - Method in class bee.Bee

exitField(Worker) - Method in class world.FlowerField
When a worker bee is done gathering from a flower, it uses this routine to indicate they are leaving, and to notify a single bees that may be waiting that they should wake up and check that there is indeed a free flower now.
